<TEXT>
The striking aspect about yesterday's dollar fall is that the effect did not
spill over into bond and equity markets. This may be partly because the main
movement was against the yen, and can be considered a spe-cific response to
Japan's political crisis.
But it also looks as though fears that the US may raise interest rates
sharply to defend the dollar are abating, despite the upward revision to
first-quarter growth. It would be unlikely, though, for the problem to go
away as easily as that. The pressures which brought about last week's
turbulence will have to be addressed eventually.
