FT  30 JUN 94 / Letters to the Editor: Time to act
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr DEREK H BROOME
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Thank heaven for Alastair Ross Goobey and his colleagues at PosTel
('PosTel vote threatens top company directors', June 27). It is high time
that all institutions tackled the scandal of executive pay and perks.
Reasoned arguments are ignored; only massive votes at AGMs will serve.
If more institutions follow the PosTel lead they will deserve the full
support of private shareholders who are otherwise easily ignored. I suggest
that any such should solicit proxies to drive home the point that executives
can no longer decide their own terms and conditions without accountability
to the owners at large.
Derek H Broome,
52 Wellington Road,
Mears Ashby,
