FT  30 JUN 94 / European Parliament seeks meeting with German Chancellor
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Parliament stepped up pressure yesterday to have a say over who
should become the new European Commission president, urging talks with
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl, Reuter reports from Brussels. Mr Egon
Klepsch, Parliament president, was preparing to contact Mr Kohl to propose
talks ahead of a summit planned for Brussels on July 15 on Mr Jacques
Delors' successor.
An early task of the parliament, which meets on July 19, will be to approve
the EU's new president. Ms Pauline Green, president-designate of the
socialist group, said parliament must know the identity of the proposed
president before it meets.
