<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUN 94 / Li Peng warns UK on trade
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China's premier yesterday warned Britain that cool political relations were
bound to affect economic ties and praised Germany for its long-standing
co-operation, Reuter reports from Beijing.
Mr Li Peng told reporters that differences between China and Britain over
democratic reforms for Hong Kong had affected overall relations. 'We hope to
see the economic and trade relations between Britain and China develop but
it is not possible to free the overall relations from the adverse effects of
the cool political relations,' he said.
Mr Li's comments came before leaving on a visit to Austria, Germany and
Romania, accompanied by economic officials and more than 30 business
leaders.
'We have long-standing co-operation with Germany, which is is our biggest
partner in western Europe,' Mr Li said. Germany is the biggest European
investor in China.
Chinese customs data for January to May show trade with Germany at Dollars
4.19bn, up 32.7 per cent over the same period in 1993.
